  "texts": [
    "For a detailed visualization of this data, please see Figure 2.",
    "The examination format for each human participant was consistent, allowing no time restrictions, enforcing a closed-book policy, and permitting the use of a basic calculator.",
    "Large Language Models Evaluated and Hyperparameter SettingThis study is dedicated to the evaluation of two extensively utilized large language models (LLMs), specifically OpenAI and Claude, with no preceding inputs.",
    "For assessing OpenAI, the GPT-4 chat box serves as a benchmark, and their latest models, GPT-3.5-turbo-1106 and GPT-4-1106-preview, are tested with a temperature setting of 1 and a maximum token value of 4,096.",
    "Claude's most recent iteration, Claude-2.1, is evaluated under a hyperparameter configuration of temperature 𝑇𝑇 = 1, 𝑡𝑡𝑡𝑡𝑝𝑝 𝑘𝑘 = 40, and 𝑡𝑡𝑡𝑡𝑝𝑝 𝑝𝑝 = 0.9.To ensure the dependability of responses from LLMs, each question is subjected to multiple trials with requests for varied responses."
